<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 8:11AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light snow showers this morning...
Scattered light snow showers will continue to move southward
through the region this morning. Visibility could fall below one
mile at times in heavier snow showers.
Any new snow accumulations this morning will be minor, generally
less than one half inch. However, a few locations near the
Highwood and Judith mountains could receive up to an inch or two
of new snow accumulation.
Those traveling this morning should be prepared for areas of
reduced visibility and slippery areas on roadways.</description>
